        <h1>üçé Food & Nutrition Program</h1>
        <p>Ensuring every child receives nutritious meals for healthy development and learning</p>
        
        <section class="nutrition-overview">
            <div class="program-description">
                <h2>Nutrition for Development</h2>
                <p>The NGO ensures children receive at least one wholesome meal per day, critical for undernourished kids who often come from situations where regular meals are not guaranteed. Good nutrition is fundamental to children's ability to learn and develop properly.</p>
                
                <p>Our nutrition program operates year-round, with special emphasis during emergencies, festivals, and school holidays when children may not have access to school meal programs.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="nutrition-services">
            <h2>Our Nutrition Services</h2>
            <div class="services-grid">
                <div class="service-item">
                    <i class="fas fa-utensils"></i>
                    <h3>Daily Nutritious Meals</h3>
                    <p>At least one wholesome meal per day for all children in our program, prepared at the center or arranged through partner programs.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-item">
                    <i class="fas fa-hands-helping"></i>
                    <h3>Thursday Langar Day</h3>
                    <p>Weekly community meal program where volunteers prepare traditional free kitchen meals and engage children with games and lessons.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-item">
                    <i class="fas fa-gift"></i>
                    <h3>Festival Food Programs</h3>
                    <p>Special meal distributions during festivals and celebrations, bringing joy and ensuring children have adequate nutrition during special occasions.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-item">
                    <i class="fas fa-shopping-basket"></i>
                    <h3>Ration Support</h3>
                    <p>Food packages and groceries provided to families, especially during emergencies and times of need.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-item">
                    <i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i>
                    <h3>Nutrition Education</h3>
                    <p>Teaching children and families about healthy eating habits, nutritional requirements, and food preparation.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-item">
                    <i class="fas fa-seedling"></i>
                    <h3>Kitchen Garden Program</h3>
                    <p>Teaching families to grow their own vegetables and herbs to supplement their nutrition and develop self-sufficiency.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="emergency-response">
